e ceremony was arranged to mark the 40th anniversary of <PERSON> Schneerson </PERSON>'s leadership of the Lubavitcher movement. Hanukkah commemorates the victory in 165 B.C. of a small band of Jews _ the <ORGANIZATION> Maccabees </ORGANIZATION> _ over the Greco-Syrian kingdom, which tried to impose its culture on the Jews and had desecrated the holy Temple in <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION>. According to legend, when the Jews entered <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION> and tried to rekindle the Temple's eternal flame, they found enough oil for one day, but the oil miraculously lasted eight days. The $ 150,000 cost of the program was paid by investor <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> O. </PERSON> <PERSON> Perelman </PERSON>, according to <PERSON> Shemtov </PERSON>. <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Rubenstein </PERSON>, a spokesman for the Lubavitchers, said anyone with a home satellite dish could have seen the ceremony. He said he did not know what cable systems carried the ceremony.
