 Dec. 26 The <LOCATION> Tulsa </LOCATION> -LRB- <LOCATION> Okla. </LOCATION> -RRB- Tribune on the <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> invasion: The <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> administration will make a tactical error if it insists that Gen. <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>, now sequestered in the quarters of the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION>'s apostolic nuncio, be turned directly over to <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> soldiers surrounding the property Let us not forget that the No. 1 objective was not to capture a man wanted on criminal charges but to oust a bloody and corrupt dictator. <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> is such an opprobrious character that it would be foolish to give him a chance to play the martyr. By demanding that the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> shove him out the door into the hands of what is, in fact, an invading army we would raise again all the anger, latent, at best, in <LOCATION> Latin </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>, over the colossus of the North. It would be far better to allow the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION>, which wants nothing of this red hot potato, to hand him over to whatever passes for the military forces in <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> not under control of <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> officers.
