 Former Romanian gymnastics star <PERSON> Nadia </PERSON> <PERSON> Comaneci </PERSON> and her companion, <PERSON> Constantin </PERSON> <PERSON> Panait </PERSON>, have been avoiding family, fellow Romanians and even some people who want to help them. One of those who have n't heard from <PERSON> Nadia </PERSON> and <PERSON> Panait </PERSON> is <PERSON> Maria </PERSON> <PERSON> Panait </PERSON>. When <PERSON> Constantin </PERSON> ran off with <PERSON> Nadia </PERSON>, he left his wife with four young children and no money. `` I thought at least he would call for Christmas,'' she said Tuesday, `` but no.'' Sightings of the couple have been reported from all over. `` I heard <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Palm </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Beach </LOCATION> from one member of my congregation,'' said Father <PERSON> Traian </PERSON> <PERSON> Pedrescu </PERSON>, pastor of The Holy Trinity Romanian Orthodox Church in neighboring <LOCATION> Mirmar </LOCATION>, a gathering place for many of the estimated 5,000 Romanians in <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>. `` But honestly, with what is happening now in our country, most of them would say, ` Who cares?''' <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> Jacki </PERSON>, executive director of the <LOCATION> U.S </LOCATION>. Gymnastics Federation, expected to hear from <PERSON> Nadia </PERSON>. After her escape from <LOCATION> Romania </LOCATION> last month, the federation received more than a dozen offers for movies, books and appearances. `` And I'm almost willing to bet that to this day, she does n't know a thing about them,'' <PERSON> Jacki </PERSON> said `` We could never reach her to tell her, so we put it out through the media.''
