<HEAD>Federal Agencies Probe Air Crash That Claimed 6 Lives</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JAMES L. ENG</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PASCO, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Federal investigators Wednesday began examining the wreckage of a commuter plane for the cause of a crash that killed all six people aboard. The twin-engine <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION> turboprop went down in a field and burst into flames just short of the runway late Tuesday while en route from <LOCATION> Seattle </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> Pasco </LOCATION> via <LOCATION> Yakima </LOCATION>. At a news conference, <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION> president <PERSON> Craig </PERSON> <PERSON> Belmondo </PERSON> raised the possibility that wing icing contributed to the crash but said it was `` much too early to speculate'' on the cause. Fire officials found ice at the crash scene but <PERSON> Belmondo </PERSON> said it had not been determined whether the ice came from the <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aerospace </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jetstream </ORGANIZATION> 31, a 19-passenger plane. The crew contacted the airline's dispatch center at the <LOCATION> Tri </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION> here within three to five miles of landing, as is routine, and gave no indication of a problem, <PERSON> Belmondo </PERSON> said. He did not know if there was any communication between the plane and the airport tower after that. <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aviation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Dave </PERSON> <PERSON> Duff </PERSON> said the plane hit 100 feet short of the runway; <PERSON> Belmondo </PERSON> said it went in 500 to 700 feet short. Investigators from the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Transportation </ORGANIZATION> safety <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> FAA </ORGANIZATION> arrived Wednesday. <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION> has deicing equipmen