<HEAD>Archbishop Says Priest's Slaying May Have Been Politically Motivated</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The slaying of a <LOCATION> French </LOCATION> priest in southeastern <LOCATION> Brazil </LOCATION> may have been politically motivated and not the work of robbers, a Brazilian archbishop said Wednesday. The Rev. <PERSON> Gabriel </PERSON> <PERSON> Felix </PERSON> <PERSON> Roger </PERSON> <PERSON> Maire </PERSON> `` had been receiving death threats for the past several months due to his work on behalf of justice and human rights for the poor,'' Archbishop <PERSON> Silvestre </PERSON> <PERSON> Scandian </PERSON> said by phone from <LOCATION> Vitoria </LOCATION>. Police found <PERSON> Maire </PERSON>, 53, shot in the chest and slumped over the wheel of his car Saturday on the outskirts of <LOCATION> Vitoria </LOCATION>, 310 miles northeast of <LOCATION> Rio </LOCATION>. Police arrested two suspects and charged them with shooting <PERSON> Maire </PERSON> during an attempted robbery. Scandian disputed the police report, saying <PERSON> Maire </PERSON>'s wristwatch and other personal items were left in the car. A bag containing his cassock and empty wallet was found about 100 yards from the scene. The Rev. <PERSON> Mauricio </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Mattos </PERSON> <PERSON> Pereira </PERSON>, of the Archdiocese's <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Peace </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION>, said three other politically motivated killings occurred in nearby towns since June `` When you try to raise the consciousness of the small, the big react,'' said <PERSON> Pereira </PERSON>. `` They want to silence all those trying to show the poor the roots of injustice.'' <PERSON> Maire </PERSON> arrived in <LOCATION> Brazil </LOCATION> in 1980 and worked in the lower-class parish of <LOCATION> Vila </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Velha </LOCATION>, eight miles south of <LOCATION> Vitoria </LOCATION>. Thousands of people attended a wake for Maire on Tuesday. The priest's body will be flown to <LOCATIO