GANIZATION> Forces </ORGANIZATION>, which numbered 15,000, and only a few hundred remained unaccounted for Among those reported arrested Wednesday was <PERSON> Vicky </PERSON> <PERSON> Amado </PERSON>, <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>'s long-time mistress. <ORGANIZATION> Southern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Command </ORGANIZATION> said Wednesday 23 Americans were killed and 322 wounded since the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> invaded. It said 297 Panamanians were killed and 123 wounded. Doctors say more than 100 civilians also died during the fighting. Meanwhile, <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION>'s ambassador to <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Jorge </PERSON> <PERSON> Turner </PERSON> <PERSON> Morales </PERSON>, resigned and asked for asylum in <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION>, a Panamanian Embassy employee said on condition of anonymity. <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> has not officially recognized the <PERSON> Endara </PERSON> government. `` I can not accept a government that was imposed under the machine guns of <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>,'' <PERSON> Turner </PERSON> <PERSON> Morales </PERSON> was quoted as saying by <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION>'s Excelsior news service.
