<DATELINE>ST. PAUL, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A report of six years of dialogue between Eastern Orthodox and Lutheran churches says several differences remain but participants found themsleves `` drawn together in Christ on the very topics on which we had anticipated greater disagreement.''
